article.description: Victoria Dunlap scored 10 points and had 10 rebounds to eclipse 1,000 for her career and Kentucky (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) easily beat Auburn 69-38.
article.headline: Wildcats take early lead, cruise past Tigers
article.linkText: Dunlap reaches milestone as UK dumps Auburn
article.story:
LEXINGTON, Ky. --  Victoria Dunlap scored 10 points and had 10 rebounds to eclipse 1,000 for her career and Kentucky (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) easily beat Auburn 69-38 on Thursday night.

Dunlap also had five assists for the Wildcats (18-4, 7-2 Southeastern Conference) and now sits in second place on the school's all-time rebound list.

Kentucky used an early 19-2 run to take control and went ahead by as many as 17 in the first half. The Tigers (13-9, 6-3) opened the second half with a 7-0 run but were unable to overcome losing the rebounding battle, 44-28, and 28 turnovers.

Brittany Henderson scored a career-high 13 points for the Wildcats, shooting 5-of-9 from the field, and added seven rebounds.

Blanche Alverson led Auburn with 12 points.

Kentucky, which has won seven straight SEC games, plays Tennessee (No. 5 ESPN/USA Today, No. 4 AP) on Monday.
